1
00:00:00,350 --> 00:00:02,685
-Hey, guys.
Thanks for taking the time
to meet with me.

2
00:00:02,685 --> 00:00:03,964
-Yeah.
-Of course, dude.

3
00:00:03,964 --> 00:00:06,098
-Um, so you have
a sketch idea for us?

4
00:00:06,098 --> 00:00:08,587
-Yeah,
I was thinking I would play,
like, a cool pope

5
00:00:08,587 --> 00:00:11,911
doing baptisms in a hot tub
and just, like,
cool stuff like that.

6
00:00:11,911 --> 00:00:13,561
That's good.
Yeah.

7
00:00:13,561 --> 00:00:15,951
-Sorry, is Jeremy listening?
-Oh, yeah.

8
00:00:15,951 --> 00:00:19,280
Jeremy's, um, training
for the big
hot dog eating contest.

9
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:22,981
July 4th is
right around the corner.
But, yes,
I promise he's listening.

10
00:00:22,981 --> 00:00:26,868
-Are you sure?
Because he seems really
locked in on those hot dogs.

11
00:00:26,868 --> 00:00:28,823
-Oh, Jeremy's the best listener
on the cast.

12
00:00:28,823 --> 00:00:33,861
-Okay. So, yeah, like,
the cool pope
would do communion,
but instead of drinking wine...

13
00:00:34,699 --> 00:00:39,165
Anyway, I was thinking
he's, like, a mobile pope.

14
00:00:39,165 --> 00:00:41,746
He's got a cool --
-It's not wet enough.

15
00:00:45,158 --> 00:00:48,312
I feel bad. I feel bad.

16
00:00:48,794 --> 00:00:52,559
-Miles, are you okay?
-Yeah. I'm sorry.
I just lost my train of thought.

17
00:00:52,559 --> 00:00:55,155
-Okay, guys,
don't worry, I got this.
The sketch is "Cool Pope."

18
00:00:55,155 --> 00:00:58,163
Your robes are made
out of jeans.
The popemobile is a skateboard.

19
00:00:58,163 --> 00:01:00,416
And for communion,
instead of wine and bread,

20
00:01:00,416 --> 00:01:02,302
you're eating pizza
and drinking...

21
00:01:02,302 --> 00:01:05,266
Both: A tallboy
of ice-cold malt liquor.

22
00:01:05,266 --> 00:01:06,302
-Oh, my God.

23
00:01:06,302 --> 00:01:09,736
-You really are
a good listener, Jeremy.
-I know. I'm the best.

24
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:12,664
-Jeremy? Jeremy!
-Oh, Jesus.
-Oh, my God!

25
00:01:12,664 --> 00:01:13,867
-Give him mouth-to-mouth!

26
00:01:13,867 --> 00:01:15,323
-Help!
-Medic!
-Help!

27
00:01:19,052 --> 00:01:20,366
-Mouth-to-mouth!
-I don't want to.

28
00:01:20,366 --> 00:01:22,524
-No, you have to!
Mouth! Mouth!

29
00:01:22,524 --> 00:01:24,523
-Can someone else --
-Mouth him!

